#!/usr/bin/env perl

=head1 NAME

mojo_lilith_receiver - Mojolicious EVE push receiver for Lilith.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

mojo_lilith_receiver daemon

mojo_lilith_receiver daemon -l http://*:8081

LILITH_CONFIG=/etc/lilith.toml mojo_lilith_receiver daemon

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Starts the Lilith EVE receiver using Mojolicious. Remote sensors push already
parsed alert rows (the output of L<Lilith/parse_eve>, one key per ingestable
column) as JSON to C<< /eve/:table >> and they are inserted into the Lilith
PostgreSQL database. This is the network counterpart to the local EVE-file
tailer driven by C<lilith monitor>.

Each alert may be pushed either as its own HTTP C<POST> or streamed as a JSON
frame over a kept-open WebSocket to the same C</eve/:table> endpoint; both use
the same bearer-key auth and the same per-row validation. A sensor running
L<App::Lilu> chooses between them with its C<lilith_websocket> config value.
See L<Lilith::Receiver> for the request and WebSocket protocol.

The config file is read from the C<LILITH_CONFIG> env var, defaulting to
C</usr/local/etc/lilith.toml>.

Supports all standard Mojolicious server commands (daemon, prefork, etc).

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<Mojolicious::Commands>, L<Lilith::Receiver>, L<Lilith::Web>

=cut

use strict;
use warnings;
use FindBin qw($Bin);
use lib "$Bin/../lib";
use Mojolicious::Commands;

Mojolicious::Commands->start_app('Lilith::Receiver');
